replyContent: I'm sorry you've not had a pleasant experience with our service. The NHS only allow 4 items on an electronic prescription which is not ideal if you take more than that but we now consciously try to send as many items together as possible. We only return prescriptions when requested if meds are out of stock of if you would prefer to collect locally.

What's worse is that another box that WAS wrapped in cold pack does not work at all (I tested it by increasing the dose by 25%).

Echo is a pharmacy that’s free to use. We cover all delivery charges, so there are no extra costs for users or the NHS. If users have an exemption, they aren’t charged for their prescription. If they don’t have an exemption, then the standard NHS charge of £9.00 applies, hence the mention of a payment platform. Hope this helps.

content: the service provided is generally very good. I have had a few issues lately with the way Echo are requesting prescriptions from my GP which have taken a bit of time to resolve.

Happy New year!!!! I used to collect my medicines from Tesco pharmacy, which was ok. great

Brilliant App. Working full time I previously struggled to get to the GP surgery and pharmacy Echo means I no longer have to worry. Service is always prompt and if there does happen to be any problems at all they contact you straight away.

One of the best app experiences; not just in how they run the service, but also in overall app usability/stability!
Great service so far.
A good app that responds to questions with human help. A few teething problems when changing over systems but soon got them sorted.

I ordered a pack of insulin on a Thursday evening. It arrived Saturday morning. 1st class delivery in this big box, complete with ice packs to keep it refrigerated. It's changed the game. Legit. It's great. No more waiting in the chemist for 15 minutes. Only one thing I would advise is that you order it two days before you know you're going to be in. Seems to be delivered within 2 working days (and Saturdays), so arrange your time accordingly. But, great app overall. 5 stars easily.

Definitely recommend! It's so easy and quick to use. I was worried about getting my medication over the Christmas period but that hasn't been a problem! My only gripe is that the mail man tries to push it through the letterbox but fails or doesn't attempt to at all so would be easier in a small jiffy bag.
Good job as usual!

So easy, so quick! I open the app, click on the medication and two days later the package is in my letterbox. It works every time. The only delay I ever had was during the initial setup on ordering the first medication. I suspect this is why some people give it bad reviews, but once it's set up, it works well for repeat prescriptions. I would never use it for one-off prescriptions, because the weak link is always going to be how quickly your GP communicates. The indispensable pocket dispenser!

content: I have been pretty disappointed with the service. I requested medication on Friday 30th March and still waiting now. I understand that the request fell in the Easter Bank Holiday but it's now over 4 working days turn around. It is approaching the second week and now I'm being informed that they are awaiting to be stocked even though the day before I was told that it was ready and waiting for dispatch. I understand that we should order medication in plenty of time but I have purchased a 'pre-pay certificate' limited to 3 months to cover me through the hayfever season so the time is limited to make sure I'm stocked up for the season. I can not put in orders too early as my GP surgery do not release prescriptions too early due to assuming I have enough medication. It was far far easier to go on my GP's website, order my meds, pick up after 48 hours then order my prescription from the supermarket pharmacy that is just round the corner. I thought this the app was to save me the time and the hassle but it seems to cause me more headache. Surely, with the technology, this should be far easier? Not happy at all....

I never, ever review apps. But this one deserves it because its changed my life... It sounds dramatic i know but with agoraphobia, anxiety, heavily pregnant and depression, this app has absolutely taken out the stress of facing the doctors and chemist. The walk is exhausting enough but then waiting around in an area that isn't very nice when it comes to drug abusers making my anxiety a whole lot worse, it's taken what was a huge strain off of me, they set an alert automatically to stop me forgetting to take my medication, they let you know personally and politely if anything is wrong which has only happened once and that was the doctors fault not echo. They keep you updated on when they've re ordered for you, it's just outright one absolutely fantastic app and service. I really can't appreciate the staff running this app enough for absolutely changing things for me for the better.

Excellent idea, easy to use and good service... 100% recommend to anyone that works and/or hasn't got the time/patience to be battling GP receptionists and Pharmacy Technicians when trying to sort out repeat prescriptions.

content: Great

content: I love this app, it's helped me out so much

Cue Echo... A couple of clicks every two months and my medication drops through the letterbox... A 21st Century solution to what should be a simple challenge; it's time for the NHS to catch up...  Well done Echo...

No more having to struggle to go all the way to my GP to get refills and most importantly having to stay without because i cant manage to leave my house when im having an episode and end up staying days and sometimes weeks without my meds. Also due to my spina bifida and incontinence I use catheters and ordering them via you guys means no more waiting for a pharmacy to order them, as they dont have them in store, again meaning that i can go days or weeks without them. This is an effecient app and allowed me to upload my HC2 exemption easily and got approved quickly. And i love it that if my medical centre takes long to provide the prescriptions or makes the mistake of issuing paper ones, you guys email me, inform me and give me alternitives whilst waiting for the meds to arrive by post. Thank you so much guys. This means everything to me and my life. :)

The only thing I'd add would be the ability to tell the app once medication had been delivered so it updates and starts the countdown to the next order. My app will often say dispatched for a few days after my medication has arrived. Overall though a fantastic, life saving app!

I'll continue to use the app in the hopes that my archaic GP practice will be better prepared next time. If I stop using the app it'll be because of the GP and not a reflection on Echo or their staff.

Unfortunately I can't get to my GP because I work during open hours so I figured, I'll go a week without my meds. Annoying but what can I do?  The app sends me a notification saying my GP has approved my request. THIS WAS A LIE. So I sat waiting for a couple of weeks and today, after being 2 weeks off of my meds, I opened the app to message saying the GP surgery I selected has told ECHO that I'm not a patient there. So now my best chance of getting my medication is to wait until Wednesday when my mother is off work and have her put in for a repeat then leave work 3 hours early (which will be unpaid) and get a taxi (which will cost £30) so I can be back in time to pick it up before surgery closes.
